			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				I must say, I played Diablo on Bnet when it was brand spanking new, BEFORE the cheaters hit really hard.  It was about the most fun a person could have. <br>  <br> Most of the time I would go on, start a game with my friend who lived a few miles away.  Call him on the phone and we could play online with eachother and talk on the phone, no silly typing during gameplay for us :) <br>  <br> It made it much easier to coordinate and such.  *sigh* I wish online play now didn't use every ounce of bandwidth or I could use Teamsound or roger wilco or something with you all or my Q3 UT buddies. <br>  <br> But I must admit, Diablo was the first real multiplayer game I played, and it was a BLAST! <br> 
